# Grafana Go backend conventions

Scoped to Go files via the `globs` above. Mirror the patterns in the package you are
editing rather than introducing new ones.

## Structure

- Business logic lives in `pkg/services/<domain>/`, not in API handlers under `pkg/api/`.
  API handlers should be thin and delegate to a service.
- Each service defines a `Service` interface in the same package, with the
  implementation alongside it (see `pkg/services/team/team.go`).
- Database access goes through `sqlstore`; do not hand-roll SQL in handlers.

## Dependency injection

- Wiring is generated with Wire. After changing a service constructor or its
  dependencies, run `make gen-go`. Wire catches circular dependencies at compile time.

## Errors & context

- Always thread `context.Context` as the first argument through service calls.
- Wrap and return errors; do not panic in request paths. Use the existing
  domain error helpers where the package provides them.

## Security

- Prevent SQL injection (use parameterized queries via sqlstore), command injection,
  and never log secrets or tokens.

## Tests

- Add `_test.go` coverage for new behavior. Run a focused test with
  `go test -run TestName ./pkg/services/<domain>/`.
